AUDIO: 'their style. For example, at Anyways, if you\'re interested in reading further, I\'ll link to this main page in the description below. Also this week, Google releases a really cool model called Gemini embedding 2. This is what'

[12:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'they call their first natively multimodal embedding model. Now, what exactly is this? You see, when we feed a prompt to GPT or another language model, it doesn\'t understand text. That text'

[12:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'needs to be converted into numbers which the model understands. Specifically, it needs to be converted into what are called embeddings. Now for multimodal models when you upload an image or an audio clip that image or audio also'

[13:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'needs to be converted into numbers. Now previously we need different models to handle different types of formats. So your text prompt would be converted into one type of embedding vectors. Your'

[13:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image would be converted into some other embedding vectors and same with audio and so on. But for this new Gemini embedding 2, it basically turns every format including text, images, videos, audio, and documents into the same'

[13:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'embedding space. So this model is able to convert all these different formats into one shared dimension which an AI model can understand. And this is super important. So, here it says for text,'

[13:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this supports a context of over 8,000 tokens. Plus, this can process up to six images per request or up to 120 seconds of video or audio or PDFs of up to six pages long. And this is super important.'

[14:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, this allows an AI model to process all these different types of documents at once. For example, let\'s say you want to look for an image that\'s found in a particular document or you want to find'

[14:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a snippet of audio that is contained in a video. With this new embedding model, you can now you can now do this. Plus, this supports over 100 languages. Now, currently, this new Gemini embedding 2'

